SIMPLE: oppression
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oppression
<hw>Op*pres"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>oppressio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of oppressing, or
state of being oppressed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which oppresses; a hardship or injustice;
cruelty; severity; tyranny.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The multitude of
<xex>oppressions</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Job xxxv. 9.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sense of heaviness or obstruction in the body or
mind; depression; dullness; lassitude; <as>as, an <ex>oppression</ex> of
spirits; an <ex>oppression</ex> of the lungs.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There gentle Sleep⟦br⟧
First found me, and with soft <qex>oppression</qex> seized⟦br⟧
My drowsed sense.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Ravishment; rape.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oppressive</ent>⟦br⟧
